  "target_response": {
    "text": "Sleeping 9.4 hours and still yawning usually points to one of two things. Either you were paying down real fatigue — a stretch of short nights, a heavy patch of training or work, or fighting something off — and one long night didn't clear the whole tab; or the extra time in bed shifted your wake-up into a deeper phase of sleep, which can leave you foggy for hours afterwards. I can't separate the two from data, since your log is manual and sleep duration is the only measurement I have. Two practical moves: hold a consistent wake time for the next few days instead of banking more lie-ins, and if the heavy-eyed feeling continues for a week despite decent nights, mention it to a clinician.",
